               <msContents>
                  <summary>Psalter. F<locus target="#2r"/>-120v: 151 Psalms of David. The word for God is not rubricated. The midpoint of the Psalms (<locus target="#65r"/>) is unmarked. The spiritual meaning of the Hebrew letters in Psalm 118 give only the names of the letters for each section. Psalm 151 is in the short version. F<locus target="#121"/>-132v: The 15 Biblical Canticles. The fourth biblical canticle is named Prayer of the mother of the mother of Samuel (an error, presumably). There is no columetric layout of text either in the 10th biblical canticle, Psalm 150 or Psalm 148. F<locus target="#132v"/>-137v: The Song of Songs, in the common edition.  F<locus target="#138r"/>-147r: The Praises of Mary, arranged for the days of the week: Monday (138r), Tuesday (138v), Wednesday (140r), Thursday (142r), Friday (144r), Saturday (145r), Sunday (146r). F<locus target="#147v"/>-151v: Gate of Light. Varia: F<locus target="#152r"/>-153v: Image of Mary, written mostly in a later hand. <locus target="#154r"/>.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1"><locus from="3r" to="152v" facs="003"/><title type="complete" ref="LIT2701Dawit"/>
