                  <additions>
                  <list>
                    <item xml:id="a1">
                    <locus target="#1v #2r" facs="002"/>
                    <desc>
                    Greeting to Gäbrä Mänfäs Qǝddus. Incipit: <foreign xml:lang="gez">ሰላም፡ ለከ፡ ገብረ፡ መንፈስ፡ ቅዱስ፡ አኪመ፡</foreign>, rotated 180 degrees from the main text in the textblock
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a2">
                    <locus target="#153r" facs="153"> f. 153r, column 1</locus>
                    <desc type="GuestText">
                    Excerpt of <title type="complete" ref="LIT2932RepCh213"/>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a3">
                    <locus target="#153r #153v #154r #154v" facs="153 154 155"/>
                    <desc>
                    Image of Gäbrä Mänfas Qǝddus, <foreign xml:lang="gez">መልክአ፡ ገብረ፡ መንፈስ፡ ቅዱስ፡</foreign>, written in a later hand. Incipit: <foreign xml:lang="gez">ሰላም፡ ሰላም፡ ለዝክረ፡ ስምከ፡ ፍሡሕ፡</foreign>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a4">
                    <locus target="#155r" facs="155"/>
                    <desc>
                    Table blessing, Table Prayer, “We beseech you,” Sä’alnakä, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ሰአልናከ፡</foreign>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e1">
                    <locus target="#1r" facs="001"/>
                    <desc>
                    pen trial, most illegible, rotated 180 degrees
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e2">
                    <locus target="#66r" facs="006"/>
                    <desc>
                    The midpoint of the Psalms is unmarked
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a5">
                    <locus target="#138v" facs="139"/>
                    <desc>
                    Scribal blessing, with Trinitarian formula, at the conclusion of the of Song of Songs
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a6">
                    <desc>
                    The spiritual meaning of the Hebrew letters in Psalm 118 give only the names of the letters for each section
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a7">
                    <locus target="#139r" facs="139"/>
                    <desc>
                    The scribe employs a technique of abbreviating the first line of the second section for some of the days of the week: for instance, Praises of Mary on Monday, each section begins with the word <foreign xml:lang="gez">ሠረ</foreign>, (abbreviation for the usual line, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ሠረቀ፡ በሥጋ፡ እምድንግል፡ ዘእንበለ፡ ዘርአ፡ ብእሲ፡ ወአድኃነነ፡</foreign>); and on Saturday he gives the abbreviation <foreign xml:lang="gez">ተፈ</foreign>, for the opening line <foreign xml:lang="gez">ተፈሥሒ፡ ኦምልዕተ፡ጸጋ፡ ተፈሥሒ፡ እስመ፡ ረከብኪ፡ ሞገሰ፡ ተፈሥሒ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ ምስሌኪ፡</foreign>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a8">
                    <desc>
                    <title type="complete" ref="LIT2000Mazmur#Chp151"/> is in the short version, lacking all four of the plusses that make up the long version
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a9">
                    <desc>
                    The fourth biblical canticle is named Prayer of the mother of the mother of Samuel (an error, presumably)
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a10">
                    <desc>
                      <title type="complete" ref="LIT2509Weddas"/> is laid out beginning with Monday and culminating in Sunday
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e3">
                    <desc>
                    The manuscript has been donated to Hope College, Holland Michigan, where it as assigned the accession number TR2017.75.490
                    </desc>
                    </item>
